ones reported the food had gone bad. After tests on storage found them all to be ruined, FC has panicked and stated all the food is gone.'),(249,64,'R&D\'s ##SUB-RD## is a weird combination of radioactive waste, gmo foods, and fertiliser. It will constantly fill the bellies of clones who eat it, but they will be extremely flatulent and constatly extrude flammable gas.'),(250,65,'##CIT-I-RD## is the current head of the Alpha Complex Space Agency. After many previous clones getting terminated due to incompetence, ##CIT-I-RD## has led a mission to the moon to ensure it goes well.'),(251,65,'Unfortunately, Mu Complex is shooting down all capsules heading to the moon, including ##CIT-I-RD##\'s.'),(252,65,'All the service groups want the honour of saving ##CIT-I-RD##.'),(253,66,'RDP ##SUB-SUN## is a project to increase the solar output of the sun. The project expects a 1000% increase in solar output, but due to an error will only increase output 0.01%.'),(254,66,'To actually deploy it, either a base on mercury or a solar ring is required to be built.'),(255,69,'Barry-B was on a troubleshooter mission, and was eaten by a mutant banana nut muffin monster.'),(256,69,'The rest of Barry-B\'s team was digested, but Barry-B survived inside the monster.'),(257,69,'The monster is a thing from the underplex, infected with a \"you are what you eat\" memetic pattern. The monster wandered through a PLC warehouse filled with luxury inter-sector transtube meals.'),(258,68,'A bunch of cockroaches wandered into an R&D lab and absorbed some chronoparticulates. They now move at multiple times faster than usual.'),(259,68,'The cockroaches are consuming food stocks at an alarming rate, and also any citizens that stand too still (all of them).'),(260,67,'A recent trip to the vaults brought back a couple of sudoku books, which were quickly disseminated and spread to the masses.'),(261,67,'The addictiveness has simultaneously meant everyone is distracted, or have finished their puzzles and are crazily searching for more.'),(262,68,'Death leopard/servants of cthulu, if the word is given, will pump an aggression gas into the megamall, causing everyone to grab weapons and kill each other. What this accomplishes is up to you.'),(263,70,'There\'s a huddle of 6 warbots located in the buffer zone between ##ZON## and  two other sectors: GDJ and WEP. They\'re actually completely loyal, and members of the very loyal Bothren.'),(264,70,'However, they also believe themselves to be holy crusaders, and have come to the conclusion that one of the neighbouring sectors are in cahoots with the commies, and are currently deciding which one it is.'),(265,70,'Destroying the warbots before they\'ve been shown to be rogue will cost ##ZON## a lot of ACCESS.'),(266,71,'A mystic group found a special incense that causes everything to look much larger than it is. This incense smoke drifted into a gold depository nearby, during an audit, causing the counters to estimate an increased gold supply by and order of magnitude.'),(267,71,'The credit isn\'t tied to the price of gold, but legacy software determines that a sudden gold price drop will crash the market.'),(268,71,'The collapse isn\'t caused specifically by the huge storage of gold, but that approximately 30k tons of gold has been stolen.'),(269,71,'Suggested cbay: 1 ton gold, 8 ACCESS'),(270,72,'WARNING: FAILURE TO SOLVE CORRECTLY WILL END COMPLEX'),(271,72,'This also means that sending any minions outside makes the sector lose some of its air, and the air value of  the sector will lower slowly over time.'),(272,72,'The easiest answer is to get a heap of hot fun syrup and deploy it into the adjoining sector, but unless the original amount is found may cause a gigantic explosion of superheated air across the planet.'),(273,72,'Additionally, several service groups are wanting more exercise, which will use up the air faster...'),(274,73,'RDP ##SUB-1## is a project to launch the sector into space. All that actually needs to happen to implement is to get the experimental rockets in place, ##SUB-1##-1, and detach the sector from anchoring beams ##SUB-A##-1 through 3. Of course, launching without the maneuvering thrusters (##SUB-1##-2) in place or the gravity generator (##SUB-1##-3) powered, they may be in some trouble.'),(275,73,'The rockets are a small amount of thrust, but each mainly consists of a wide-angle anti-gravity beam. Simply destroying the rockets will still cause the sector to float, but won\'t get it into space.'),(276,74,'There\'s a particularly large IR market at ##LOC-1##, which was overrun by INFRAREDs. Now one tenth of the population is equipped with cone rifles. (Better watch that happiness index)'),(277,75,'NOTE: Designed to be used if the sector is recently cut off from other sectors. One large part of efficiency is inter-sector travel. With that no longer happenning, the efficiency index had plummeted from 120% to 65%.'),(278,75,'Of course, this lack of inter-sector travel isn\'t directly responsible for the drop on paper, but affects every industry and service group.'),(279,76,'Metal stocks aren\'t actually low. However, Friend Computer is gearing up for a new phase of expansion and requires a large amount of materials for the future projects.'),(280,76,'CPU wants to connect with earth. AF wants to nuke a passing comet and harvest that. PS wants He3 (probably from the moon). PLC doesn\'t have space for the extra metal. IS wants to punish anyone that talks with other complexes.'),(281,75,'AF wants to get in fights. R&D wants more DNA for the clone banks. CPU wants more paperwork. IS wants jobs for checkpoints and cavity searchers. TS wants more 949M-77/OV replacement parts (lightbulbs with filaments built only in LIT sector).'),(282,77,'Mining has halted due to Phlegms underneath, and FC still wants massive expansion. The mining teams haven\'t reported back, and PLC doesn\'t know what\'s wrong.'),(283,77,'If the UVs call the missing mining teams they get the phlegms on the line, who attempt to ransom the mining teams and equipment in return for passage to Earth.'),(284,78,'Citizen Barry-I-WRU has been sent to ensure the sector meets minimum standards in all indicies. Failing to meet these stardards will means ##ZON## will be disowned by the main complex.'),(285,78,'Barry-I-WRU is more than happy to be bribed heavily, and knows that a poor report probably means the complete destruction of the sector.'),(286,79,'Power services found an egg while delving the vaults, and stored it in one of the reactors. The warm glow made it hatch, and now there\'s a baby velociraptor on the loose.'),(287,77,'PLC wants teams and equipment back. TS wants the equipment to disappear, and CPU wants the teams to disappear.'),(288,78,'AF wants to stage a live fire demonstration, and IS wants tongue print, foot print, and finger print from the head of the delegation.'),(289,80,'SETUP: Set Happiness index high and Compliance index low'),(290,80,'Citizens are far too lazy and haven\'t been outputting. Friend Computer has adjusted nominal happiness levels lower, and efficiency levels to be higher.'),(291,80,'Of course, trying to actually get them to stop being lazy is another matter.'),(292,81,'SETUP: One of the HPs has Sport-I-CUS in their basement, and has bet against the home funball team. Inform them of the need to clean up their tracks in a private message (video, forensic, and witness statements)'),(293,81,'Due to the massive amount of cloning (fan and funball accidents), Sport-I-CUS is on his 30th clone. The templates\' been cleaned up a few times, but actually cloning him again will cost a cool 8 ACCESS.'),(294,81,'A funball game is set to take place in an hourcycle. Ensure several HPs have pre-existing bets for and against the game.'),(295,82,'BACC: Bake A (pretty) Cake Contract'),(296,82,'The cake is the feature of Sting-U-YYY\'s party tonight, but hasn\'t been completed due to another HP sabotaging it.'),(297,82,'The instruction manual for cooking the cake was stolen by Free Ent, then from them by the HP. Without that manual the cake can\'t be cooked.'),(298,82,'The cake is also extremely mutagenic and will push the mutant powers of anyone who eats it.'),(299,83,'The phlegms have been busy stealing armaments. Last night both groups did huge heists and have been preparing for war.'),(300,84,'The romantics built a mirror maze at ##LOC##. Free Ent saw the opportunity and started charging for entrance.'),(301,84,'Death leopard are stalking the maze and scaring patrons. Purge then went nuts and started killing clones in the maze.'),(302,84,'A single laser shot is going to hit *someone* in that maze.'),(303,84,'Also, PLC have been harvesting the bodies that PURGE have been dumping, not asking where they\'re coming from. HPD wants to find out.'),(304,85,'Several AF scouts who are also mystics had a bad trip yesterday and started seeing petbots and giant monsters. They reported it before they realised what had happened.'),(305,85,'In order to not embarrass the SG, the scouts continued to report the elusive beasts. Other scouts also joined in, worried they had missed something and would be demoted.'),(306,85,'Now the entire scout section is reporting dangerous four legged beasts in the corridors and air vents.'),(307,85,'Some \'sighting\' locations: ##LOC-1##, ##LOC-2##, ##LOC-3##.'),(308,85,'In the meantime, PS actually *did* release something nasty from one of the vaults, but so far it\'s purely underground. If it doesn\'t get cleaned up fast it gets into the complex and there really *is* a problem.'),(309,86,'All the bots have been converted, either by disaster, choice, or otherwise.'),(310,86,'This means all the scrubbots are no longer working and filth is piling up. Additionally, all the garbagetruckbots aren\'t collecting garbage.'),(311,87,'So, things are bad. AF is heavily underequipped, the transtubes aren\'t used since the bots are gone, and law and order is in the bucket.'),(312,87,'In order to re-unite the complex, FC has demanded a field test. If the threat\'s just a joke, FC won\'t be happy. It needs to be something that actually send the complex into a crisis.'),(313,87,'Of course, all the service groups have differing ideas of what needs to happen.'),(314,88,'The \'multiple commie superweapons deployed\' are just earthquakes, and loud boxes occasionally dropping.'),(315,88,'The earthquakes are caused due to the fact that Alpha Complex is small, and inside a house. Alpha Complex is so small, that the average person\'s footstep is causing an earthquake.'),(316,88,'The reason this wasn\'t a problem before is that the attic, the location where tiny Alpha Complex is, is usually is untouched... however the homeowners are doing some spring cleaning.'),(317,88,'There is no reasonable way to correct the earthquakes, and the directives given for each \'potential cause\' a not related to the outside world. Best way for players to avoid punishment is to think of something creative, or add earthquakes and loud noises to \'natural outside production\'.'),(318,88,'If you are not following \'Tiny Complex\' campaign, then disregard notes 2-3 and amend note #1 by swapping out\' loud boxes occasionally dropping\' with \'loud thunderstorms.\''),(319,88,'By: Ndo360'),(320,89,'The Brain And Reality Neuraliser Engaging Yowler robot (codename BARNEY) is a highly effective propaganda bot'),(321,89,'However, a commie cell modified the program, and it\'s now spouting commie propaganda.'),(322,90,'All of the service groups have been infected with a new kind of disease, called Garfielditus. A medical study will reveal they suffer from a peculiar form of jaundice that makes their skin orange (thus making all the IR and R treasonous), makes them extremely slothful, and as the bacteria feeds on yeast and cheese products, a desire for lasagne. '),(323,90,'FC is unaware of this, but he knows something is up. The details of the disease were stored in a crisis report (that also details every single secret society activity that day cycle), but yesterday the only HP on duty was Garfi-U-ELD and hes patient zero so he cant help. R&D developed the bug, tech services released it, and CPU forgot to publish the crisis report, so those are the most affected service groups. If the report isnt recovered, the disease cured, or there isn\'t a way to trick FC into thinking the situation is under control, FC will abandon the sector, terminate all the citizens, or do something else over the top like declare all activities were secret society activities. '),(324,90,'Od-I-IIE is currently holed up in AF, Nerm-O-LLL is in CPU, and JonArb-U-CLE is in R&D.'),(325,91,'Old motivational workplace tapes from the 90\'s are discovered, with messages like \'how to avoid peer pressure in the workplace\', \'friendship is magic\' and so on. '),(326,91,'They begin to circulate among secret societies as propaganda, only to be discovered by R&D after being mistakenly filed. They extracted the \'happy feeling\' chemical created in the human brain by Charm mutants (has the same effect as the \'Charm\' mutation but only when sprayed), and turned it into a chemical spray form during riots earlier in the week. A few trials were approved by Friend Computer, to ensure they won\'t happen again, because loyalty in the sector is very, very low without it. '),(327,91,'Either because of the tapes, or the chemical being sprayed around, everyone in the sector is a good, clean-cut christian boyclone or girlclone, and won\'t even say anything ruder than \"Oh heck\", let alone actually root out traitors. Citizen Bob-R-OSS, who teaches clones how to be creative, has taken off as a result and even supplanted Teela-O, to Friend Computer\'s anger. '),(328,91,'Also because everyone\'s so nice and helpful, the paperwork is getting done more efficiently. People may mistake \'doing paperwork\' with \'being friendly\' since everyone\'s so gosh darn ready to help out. '),(329,91,'Note: CPU aren\'t getting jackboots out because they\'re working on more important, riot stopping paperwork. If they get back on the jackboots, things start to fall apart.'),(330,91,'Note: PLC aren\'t overstocked on jackboots, they just haven\'t had paperwork come through for them.'),(331,91,'Note: (R&D/PS) PA121-C4N is in transit/spraying. If it\'s stopped, and there\'s no evidence to show FC that it was the same as charm, he will demand to know why the HP stopped such a vital field test of a new clone happiness chemical. If they *do* convince him it\'s a good idea to stop it, loyalty index plummets, and Friend Computer holds them responsible. '),(332,92,'For once, the crisis is exactly what it seems. Jazzer-U is unhappy the song makes fun of him and wants it removed.'),(333,92,'HPD, AF, and IS are all fighting over ##CIT-Y-1##, the one who made the original video. ##CIT-Y-1## works for tech services.'),(334,92,'If the blockchain project goes ahead before the song is completely scrubbed, the song makes it onto the blockchain and can\'t be removed without a heavily disruptive amount of effort.'),(335,92,'Tech services are performing network maintenance, and things should go down intermittently.'),(336,93,'A rogue terrorist group going by the moniker \"GREEN Giggle Gang\" have been using their positions to print pages of bad jokes off under higher up\'s orders.'),(337,93,'This widespread increase in printing has caused a huge increase in paper production, leading to the widespread logging of nearby trees.'),(338,93,'The oxygen levels have now dropped heavily in INFRARED areas, causing widespread narcolepsy and lack of efficency.'),(339,94,'The B\'s are dying. BLUE clearance citizens who managed the food vats are dying due to wrongful terminations.'),(340,94,'Introduction of new commie flagging keywords has made \"blue\" and \"sad\" synonyms, and as we all know, anybody who isn\'t happy is a commie mutant traitor.'),(341,94,'Everyone\'s lethargic due to lack of food, and the Exercise Index is only above board because AF and TS are being made to run laps to keep it out of the red.'),(342,95,'Yesterday, a HP changed 2 + 2 = 5, because they were tasked with recovering 5 items but only got 4. As a result, FCs computation is off, and anytime he needs to say four he says five.'),(343,95,'This includes the word for, such as Five what reason did you order this, citizen? and Negative citizen, the reason five your actions was your own incompetence.'),(344,95,'Increasing surveillance only increases the number of clones FC can miscount. The more teams operating (i.e. not dead) also increases his errors.'),(345,96,'Work order ##SUB-FLAV## is a directive to rotate out Soybean from the 31 Official Flavors, and introduce liquorice instead.'),(346,96,'This was done by ##CIT-V-HPD## (HPD) who hates soybean, but also to get at their rival ##CIT-V-PS## (PS) who loves soybean.'),(347,96,'Vitals: ##CIT-V-HPD##. Location: ##LOC-VHPD##. Societies: Psion, The Movement. '),(348,96,'Vitals: ##CIT-V-PS##. Location: ##LOC-VPS##. Societies: Anti-Mutant, Free Enterprise'),(349,96,'Things that need to be done: Sell off old stock, rotate advertising campaigns, retrofit flavour processing.'),(350,97,'Citzen Sherl-O-CKH has a weird variation of deep thought that allows him to solve crimes at an unprecedented level.'),(351,97,'These crimes are all treason done in the line of duty, so productivity is actually falling.'),(352,97,'Also, citizen Mor-I-ART-1, criminal mastermind, and Sherl-O-CKH doppleganger, is at large and out to discredit Sherl-O-CKH.'),(353,97,'Any time Sherl-O-CKH works with a team, he quickly finds and reports treason, found or unfound. If it\'s Mor-I-ART-1, he creates treason of a far worse scale.'),(354,97,'Mor-I-ART-1 has also stolen a bunch of things: Experimental implants, mutagens, explosives, and a WMD. The associated secret societies are pissed.'),(355,98,'R&D made a \"sea monkey\" toy/pet, sold to PLC to market at scale, but CPU kept putting off actually doing testing and paperwork (see the directive), so the PLC worker who had to look after the stuff just dumped it down the sink so he didn\'t have to bother any more.'),(356,98,'Problem: R&D failed to realise what they\'d actually made was a carnivorous form of krill. These got into the water supply, multiplied, then started getting consumed by citizens. Citizens are now being eaten alive from the inside. Hygiene index dropping low was a result of the contamination of the water, and maybe due to people bleeding or emitting waste. Clones are overeating because it suppresses what they think are hunger pangs. What is actually happening is the krill are eating the food instead of the clone at that time. This is leading to a shortage in food.'),(357,98,'Optional extra: the krill also spontaneously transform into other sea life on occasion. Sometimes sharks burst from the chests of INFRAREDs. Cool!'),(358,98,'Thank: Scarnonc-U-NTS, GimmieTend-U-IES'),(359,99,'5 minutes later, announce: An additional 300 unidentified mutants are now present in Yellow-Clearance Rec-room ##SUB-99##. Please register mutants as soon as possible.'),(360,99,'It\'s a Minecraft one-shot. Zombie Pigmen (also known as naked anthropomorphic Pig Citizens) are coming out of a Neither Portal and occupying the Rec-Room. Will only attack if provoked.'),(361,99,'The glowstone from the Nether is now being used as an ingredient in paint to brighten up the walls and is currently trialled by R&D on infrared citizens awake. This raises efficiency but is causing the compliance index to fall.'),(362,99,'The weight of the Neither portal is causing the floor beneath it to vibrate so everyone within a couple of meters of the portal sounds like they are being shaken. If the portal is not destroyed within 2 hours, lava will begin to pour out of it.'),(363,99,'Additionally, the financial system is under heavy burden, as a single yellow citizen ##CIT-Y-99## is taking golden swords and selling them on ebay'),(364,99,'UV payments will still function normally, however all lower clearance citizens experience issues with their transactions.'),(365,99,'Recommended Ebay listing: Golden sword 1 access. List it 7 times.'),(366,99,'Note: the tree is a minecraft tree. They cut the trunk but the rest didn\'t fall. The mystics were growing their drugs in there'),(367,99,'Note: There is a cloning machine in the nether spitting out the zombie pigmen'),(368,100,'The top levels of sector ABA house one of several water waste treatment plants. These plants treat the water before exposing it to several days of direct sunlight, the UV rays kill any remaining bacteria that was missed from the treatment. However, the weather has been cloudy over the past days and to make everything worse an alien spacecraft has arrived, blocking the treated water tanks. The alien spacecraft has stopped here on multiple occasions so InSec has been covering it up. The aliens have mistaken the water tanks and the Warbots on the surface to be a something like the human equivalent of a dog park (water tanks marking the parks parameter and Warbots being the pets). The Spacecraft will not move unless it is fired upon, one of their alien pets gets sick (they will take it to an alien vet) or the plant managers finish chatting with the aliens (All the plant employees are registered mutants, which is why the aliens feel comfortable talking to them).'),(369,100,'Because the exposed water tanks aren\'t being exposed to UV rays, the water still carried bacteria and has infected yellow to blue citizens. A fecal virus has developed from the bacteria and is causing diarrhea in these clearance levels. Due to the drugs inside the mandated infrared, red and orange water supply the bacteria has been neutralised.'),(370,100,'The Roast Incident came from CNNNN\'s Conan-O-BRN\'s Fireside Chat segment where the guest and host had a roast dinner interlude in the middle of show to serve as a toilet break. When it was originally canceled, it served as inspiration for a large arson attack, carried out by a ton of unhappy infrared across the complex. Treason was committed left and right, only subsiding when the show was put back on. Recently promoted media managers want to shake things up a bit and are not aware of this issue. If the show doesn\'t meet their expectations, they will cancel it (GM decides what those expectations are as well as who the guest is as the managers would have selected someone who meets their expectations).'),(371,100,'Note: R&D\'s weird signal is coming from the warbots around the waste treatment plant requesting backup, because alien pets play hard'),(372,100,'Note: HPD scrubbots are working overtime removing feces from sick citizen\'s homes'),(373,100,'Note: Using bicyles to power the fireside chat is a massive cost saving measure'),(375,100,'Note: TD\'s Ketchum-R-ASH is a little insane. His power is teleport a Yellow Clearance Citizen to his location, he believes them to be a monster that he can control, that isn\'t the case.'),(376,100,'GM TODO: Make sure you come up with the special guest for the chat! Remember that they\'re missing'),(377,101,'The Romatics have recently rediscovered nobility and now believe everything would be better if everyone had a crown on their head. They created the \"King\'s Cough\" virus which is transmitted via coughing and causes the top of the skull to grow spikes, making them a mutant. Sector DED has been locked down due to an outbreak among the IRs but everyone has been relatively calm, with rations being supplied by neighbouring sectors.'),(378,101,'However, a TV show Sammy Simplicity (a show which helps citizens get over pretty basic fears like heights/communists etc.) had been tasked with showing a new PetBot rollout is safe for citizens. The PetBot has a lot of sharp edges due to a rushed production cycle but has a 1L hand sanitiser dispenser attached to help keep hygiene up. The IR on the show who was meant to interact with this PetBot panicked, then the PetBots bugged out and vanished from the studio. Higher clearance levels proceeded to assume the worst from everyone running around the sector and begun stockpiling toilet paper, but this has caused public and private toilet hygiene to spiral out of control.'),(379,101,'Anyone from UV to Indigo has got a toilet paper stockpile, but PLC has installed a bidet system in their clearance-level bathrooms. '),(380,101,'Having heard about the sudden toilet paper shortage due to the PetBot Incident, Green to Red have taken all the paperwork piles (regardless of what is on it) instead as a toilet paper substitute, they also have bidets.'),(381,101,'IRs do not want to go anywhere near the toilets due to the PetBot scare, so PLC has bribed Power Services to raise the temperature of the sector to cause citizens of all clearances to shed their uniforms, they are re-purposing these discarded uniforms into nappies for the IRs. This temperature increase is dehydrating the citizens, impacting the water supply (so bidets will stop working) and the supply of Cold/Hot Fun is starting to dry up. Citizens could soon be stockpiling water and may cause damage to the plumbing.'),(382,101,'The final problem regards the cloning tubes, HPs are outside sector DED so they are unaffected if they are terminated but anyone inside sector DED cannot be re-cloned. The virus was built into the clone templates by the Romatics. Clone Arrangers launched a cyber attack to stop this so their future clone tanks were saved but were taken out by CPU before the IR templates could be fixed. If traces of the virus inside the clone template are not removed completely, they will reinfect all the new clones.'),(383,101,'Note: R&D\'s cure for the crown cough is to cut the spikes off with bolt cutters'),(384,101,'Note: There is a bug in the cloning template causing new clones to fall asleep mid sentence.'),(385,101,'Note: The mystics alcohol will indeed ward off the cough, but will make everyone drunk'),(386,101,'Thank: SPBrian'),(387,100,'Thank: SPBrian'),(388,102,'Teela-O was reported missing by a medical doctor Greg-V-EIR after she failed to present for a medical check-up. However, Greg is responsible for her disappearance, Teela-O requested a lung extension from him so she could project her voice louder and sing for longer. Greg initially experimented this surgery on IRs using a MedBot, some IRs now have super extended lungs and some died in the process, so were recloned. The MedBot is currently performing the surgery on Teela, but is out of anaesthetic so Teela will die one hour in if not found and stabilised. Greg actually is more of a manager then a medical practitioner but is scared to explain himself and doesn\'t want to be terminated. Teela also does not have any clones remaining, so if she is not recovered in time the HPs will need to try something else as her new album needs to be released today.'),(389,102,'Citizens are becoming disloyal due to hearing loss from the loud construction noises in the housing district. These houses are all being renovated as surveys have found that new dwellings for citizens create a sustainable increase to the happiness index. The destruction of the old houses can be stopped to halt the deafening blasts, but the HPs must address the problems with the houses. These problems are 1.)Wallpaper is coming off the walls, re-glue it or paint over it instead 2.) Fireplaces are too cold as the heating element is broken. 3.) Access is denied to some houses as the security scanner is looking through old records and newer clones do not exist.'),(390,102,'The Recycling Plant is surrounded by a picket line, these citizens forming this line are users of the recycled plastics  and are conducting a sympathy strike. They are losing money as the supply of plastics has been erratic and they haven\'t been able to meet demand for plastic straws and cutlery at the Canteens. The line is made up of these plastic suppliers and a WarBot to improve their negotiation chances. Citizens inside the plant (who the plastic users think are having a hard time working long hours) have been making raincoats out of the plastic as the fire sprinklers keep going off in the sector and everyone is getting cold. The Fire sprinklers are going off due to Sargent Opal-G-OPI, who is on the run from a Armed Forces\' Court Marshall as they discovered that he possessed a mutant power to make smokescreens which are triggering the smoke detectors and setting off the sprinklers.  '),(391,102,'Teela-O\'s studio and private server is hidden in ##LOC-102-SERV##.'),(392,102,'Note: Medbot #348-B is the one doing Teela-O\'s lung extensions'),(393,102,'Thank: SpBrian');
